The paper deals with distributed algorithms for reachability and shortest path problems in directed unweighted graphs, which are topics that fall under the categories of Distributed Computing (cs.DC) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). The algorithms are designed for the Broadcast CONGEST model, which is a network model that falls under the category of Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI). The paper also involves analyzing the time complexity of the algorithms, which falls under the category of Algorithms (cs.AL). Finally, the paper deals with graph theory and the properties of graphs, which falls under the category of Computational Geometry (cs.CG).
